c Paths in Production Code\n\n| Severity | Location | Issue |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| **High** | `crates/reme-storage/src/lib.rs` (30+ sites) | `.expect(\"mutex poisoned\")` on every lock acquisition ŌĆö poisoned mutex crashes entire client. Node-side code (`mailbox_store.rs`) handles this correctly with `map_err` |\n| **High** | `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs:459,521` | `.expect(\"invariant: is_update implies entry exists\")` ŌĆö if mDNS emits `PeerUpdated` for unknown peer (race condition with mdns-sd), discovery controller task panics and LAN discovery silently dies |\n| **Medium** | `crates/reme-message/src/wire.rs:75,81` | `bincode::encode_to_vec().unwrap()` in `WirePayload::encode()` ŌĆö fallible call wrapped in infallible API, panics in send path |\n| **Medium** | `crates/reme-message/src/tombstone.rs:162,168` | Same pattern in `to_wire_bytes()` and `to_bytes()` |\n| **Medium** | `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs:1555` | `.expect(\"MQTT pool always initialized\")` ŌĆö crashes TUI if MQTT pool not available |\n| **Low** | `crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs:293,302,394,445,659` | `dag_state.lock().unwrap()` ŌĆö inconsistent with storage's `.expect()` and node's `map_err` |\n\n### Concurrency Issues\n\n| Severity | Location | Issue |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| **Medium** | `crates/reme-discovery/src/mdns_sd.rs` | `stop_advertising` releases lock, awaits unregister, re-acquires lock to set `advertising = false` ŌĆö TOCTOU race where `start_advertising` could succeed then get clobbered |\n| **Low** | `crates/reme-transport/src/mqtt_target.rs` | MQTT event loop spawned as detached task; on target drop + recreate, brief parallel event loop race |\n| **Low** | `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs` | Cleanup loop has no cancellation token ŌĆö dropped on shutdown with no final WAL checkpoint |\n\n### Missing Validation\n\n| Severity | Location | Issue |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| **Low** | `apps/client/src/config.rs` | No validation that `max_peers` is